Na8-10Al6Si6O24S2-4 containing a blue cubic mineral called lazurite (the major
component in lapis lazuli). Some chloride is often present in the crystal
lattice as well. The blue color of the pigment is due to the S3− radical anion,
which contains an unpaired electron

