toxic materials based on lead or chromium, and by 2006 it
had become the most commonly used corrosion inhibitor.[1]
Zinc phosphate coats better on a crystalline structure
than bare metal, so a seeding agent is often used as a
pre-treatment. One common agent is sodium pyrophosphate.[2]

